Match values not in vector

Source: R/operators.R
not-in.Rd

Infix operator returning TRUE for elements of left operand (lhs) not found in right operand (rhs). Equivalent to !(lhs %in% rhs).

Usage

lhs %!in% rhs

Examples


"April" %!in% month.name
#> [1] FALSE
"Junvember" %!in% month.name
#> [1] TRUE

some_letters <- sample(letters, 10)
letters[letters %in% some_letters]
#>  [1] "c" "d" "e" "k" "n" "o" "q" "t" "v" "y"
letters[letters %!in% some_letters]
#>  [1] "a" "b" "f" "g" "h" "i" "j" "l" "m" "p" "r" "s" "u" "w" "x" "z"
